name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text:
My #AmericaCOMPETES amendments closely align w/what I believe the U.S. must do to better compete w/China & the world. Read my updated China White Paper, which is clear-eyed about the challenges China poses to U.S. global leadership.

https://t.co/4ylER3RsOx

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text:
Since 1946, Fulbright exchanges have been a vital tool for deepening U.S. understanding of China.
 
My amendment w/@RepDonBeyer restores exchanges w/China to build U.S. expertise on China & enable Chinese participants to experience the real U.S. & benefits of academic freedom.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text:
China’s #BRI invests in digital infrastructure projects around the world that often lack high standards of privacy & data security.
 
My amendment helps the U.S. compete by prioritizing U.S. support for high standard projects like expansion of wireless networks in The Gambia.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text:
The U.S. has fallen behind as a leader in refugee resettlement.
 
As Congress takes steps to protect Uyghur refugees, my amendment ensures admission of Uyghurs does not inadvertently take away opportunities from other vulnerable refugee groups from other parts of the world.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text:
In addition, three of my amendments to the bill were just adopted that ⬇️

✅ Restore U.S. leadership on human rights
✅ Invest in high-quality digital infrastructure
✅ Strengthen Fulbright exchanges & people-to-people ties

For more on my amendments, keep scrolling ⬇️

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats @HHSGov The #BuildBackBetter Act enables all Washingtonians to benefit from the economic recovery by putting more people to work, empowering working families, ensuring seniors can afford prescription drugs, building more affordable housing & combating the climate change crisis.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats @HHSGov Northwest Washington is defeating the pandemic, but it has not yet been defeated; the economy is recovering, but it has not yet recovered.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats @HHSGov The #BuildBackBetter Act means that, in Washington state, 108,000 uninsured people will gain health care coverage & 89,300 Washingtonians will on average save hundreds of dollars per year.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats @HHSGov The #BuildBackBetter Act helps older Americans access affordable hearing care by expanding Medicare.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats @HHSGov The #BuildBackBetter Act closes the Medicaid coverage gap to help millions of Americans gain health insurance & extends through 2025 the American Rescue Plan’s health insurance premium reductions for those who buy coverage on their own.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats @HHSGov The #BuildBackBetter Act caps insulin copays at $35 per month for Medicare beneficiaries & creates a new, out-of-pocket cap of $2,000 on what seniors pay for their drugs in Medicare Part D.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act empowers @HHSGov to negotiate directly with drug companies to lower drug prices for the nearly 1.4 million Medicare beneficiaries in Washington state.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act will lower prescription drug prices for seniors. Currently, Medicare is prohibited by law from negotiating with pharmaceutical companies over the price of medications. Seniors have long paid too much for prescriptions.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act includes provisions that increase the availability of high-quality housing through the construction & rehabilitation of more than 1 million affordable units nationwide, creating jobs in construction & more housing for Washingtonians.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act makes a $151 billion investment toward affordable housing solutions nationwide, including $24 billion for critical rental assistance.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act improves access to affordable housing in Washington state, where ~487,000 Washington renters spend more than 30% of their income on rent, & homeownership remains out of reach for many.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act enables Washington’s 34 public community colleges to benefit from federal grants to develop & deliver innovative training initiatives & expand successful existing initiatives.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act contains $10 billion for the full replacement of lead pipes in drinking systems throughout the country.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act invests $20 billion nationwide in workforce development initiatives that prepare Washingtonians for in-demand jobs in clean energy, child care, public health, manufacturing & IT.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act extends & expands clean energy tax credits to invest $300+ billion to support clean energy investments & deployment, improve energy efficiency & encourage vehicle electrification.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act means well-paying green jobs for Northwest Washington. BBB establishes a nationwide 300,000+ member Climate Conservation Corps that puts Washingtonians to work conserving public lands, bolstering local resilience & addressing climate change.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act is the largest single effort to combat the climate crisis in US history, investing $555 billion over 10 years to cut pollution, reduce energy costs & create well-paying jobs to ensure the US leads the clean energy economy.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act permanently authorizes the first-ever national paid family & medical leave guarantee for US workers for up to four weeks.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act extends the expanded #ChildTaxCredit that cut childhood poverty in half nationwide. In October, an estimated 76,000 #WA02 families received a #ChildTaxCredit payment.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act enables Washington to expand access to free, high-quality preschool for 181,000+ additional 3- & 4-year-olds per year & increase the quality of preschool for children who are already enrolled.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: @HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act provides access to safe, affordable child care for 470,000+ WA children per year for families earning under 2.5 times the state’s median income.

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text:
@HouseDemocrats The #BuildBackBetter Act makes bold, FDR-like investments in my priorities for the Second District:

✅ Quality, Affordable Child Care
✅ Well-Paying Clean Energy Jobs
✅ More Affordable Housing
✅ Lower Drug Costs & Health Care Prices

name: Rep. Rick Larsen
tweet_text: .@HouseDemocrats just passed the #BuildBackBetter Act, legislation that creates well-paying union jobs, drives long-term economic recovery & growth & enables NW Washington to combat the climate change crisis. BBB enables all Washingtonians to benefit from economic recovery. ⬇️
